          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1651596367556-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the vegetables are softening, dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Top, tail, peel, then grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1651596373065-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1651596373065-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1651596373065-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1651596373065-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1651596373065-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garam masala </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> then cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and begins to coat the vegetables</p><p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat – these are your <strong>curried vegetables</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1651596395598-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1651596395598-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1651596395598-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1651596395598-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1651596395598-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved chicken breast strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>remaining garam masala </strong>and<strong> remaining ground turmeric </strong>and cook for 10-12 min, turning once halfway, until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Add your <strong>tortillas</strong> to a plate and pop them in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 20 secs or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1651596469185-x200.jpg",
